	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1"/>
				<p><addressee>Rev. Mr Leeser</addressee> <placeName>Philada</placeName>&#33;</p>
				<p>Rev. Sir&#33;  Our heartfelt thank to you for your kindly<lb/> regard of our&#39;n<add>&#63;</add> by sending the Occident to us.<lb/>  Please accept my name as a subscriber to your<lb/> far spread Paper.  In about two weeks I shall call<lb/> at your office for to pay the same.</p>
				<p>Our new Synagogue was duly consecrated&#44; the notices about<lb/> the same&#44; which are given in by following Paper you<lb/> will please and copy in the Occident&#44; with the especially<lb/> remark&#44; that in the <sic>evining</sic> after the Consecration the<lb/> members of the Congregation <sic>maid</sic> in a body a visit to me<lb/> where <persName>Mr Burnstein</persName>&#44; a well educated young man <del>maid</del> delivered<lb/> an eloquent Address and representing to me one Dozen<lb/> of fine silver table spoons&#44; engraved in a <sic>verry</sic> remark<lb/> able manner.  Our congregation is in a prosperous condition<lb/> and by coming of <persName>Mr Lissner</persName> of <placeName><sic>Sax Meiningen</sic></placeName>&#44; for who<lb/> we wrote to take charge of the Ministership we shall<lb/> surely get a fine <add>Hebrew</add>.</p>
			<p rend="indent(9)">Yours Sir most obedient</p>
			<p rend="indent(9)"><persName role="author">Michael Putzel</persName>.</p>
				<p><placeName>Easton</placeName>&#44; <date>April 25. 1851</date>.</p>
				<p>P.S. The Officers elect by the last</p>
				<p>G. M. are&#58;</p>
				<list type="simple">
				<head></head>
					<item rend="indent(1)"><persName>M. Putzel</persName>  Pres.</item>
					<item rend="indent(1)"><persName>Israel Ullman</persName> Treasurer</item>
					<item rend="indent(1)"><persName>Liebman Traugott</persName>  Secy.</item>
					<item rend="indent(1)"><persName>Moses Cohn</persName> &#38; <persName>Henry Ballinger</persName>  Trustees.</item>
				</list>
				<p>and then 6 Deputies&#44; which officers have to lead the transactions of <add>Hebrew</add>.</p>
			<pb n="2"/>
				<p><addressee>Rev. Mr. Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Editor of the Occident</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)"><placeName>118 South Fourth Street</placeName>.</p>
			<p rend="indent(3)"><placeName>Philada.</placeName></p>
			
